quran[3]{c,v,t}:
  63,9,"O ye who believe! let not your property nor your children divert you from the remembrance of God, - for whosoever does that, they are those who lose"
  63,10,"But expend in alms of what we have bestowed upon you before death come on any one of you, and he says, 'My Lord! wouldst thou but have respited me till an appointed time nigh at hand, then would I surely give in charity and be among the righteous"
  63,11,"But God will never respite a soul when its appointed time has come: and God of what ye do is well aware"